inline_comments.message:
This class is used by participants to set the statistics so I think it's better to allow access using the Lombok generated getters and setters. The copy constructor is used during the marshalling of the ParticipantStatus message for DMaaP.

But when the participant is populating the ControlLoopStatistics object, I think it's better to do:

ControlLoopStatistics clStates = new ControlLoopStatistics();
clStats.setUpTime(12345);
clStates.setLastStart(98665);

and so on, I think that would be easier for developers.

Maybe we need some more cute construction like automatically setting the timestamp on object instantation so this could change as we move on with the work.
